126
00:09:32,890 --> 00:09:37,240
Among the four ancient forms of art, I respect GO the most.

127
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:39,110
Because for human beings,

128
00:09:39,110 --> 00:09:41,550
it's the most complicated and unpredictable form of art.

129
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:43,290
To be able to speak with such amazing GO players

130
00:09:43,290 --> 00:09:47,240
has been on my wishlist for the show for a long time.

131
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:50,160
Don't worry about drawing the viewers' attention.

132
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:53,300
Other than the famous players from Jiuzhou Hall,

133
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:56,770
because such celebrity players like Jo Yeon Hoon and Kato Kiyomasa, are also really popular in China.

134
00:09:56,770 --> 00:09:59,710
I believe this production will bring everyone

135
00:09:59,710 --> 00:10:01,860
some joyful and meaningful conversations.

136
00:10:01,860 --> 00:10:04,350
This new series will be called

137
00:10:04,350 --> 00:10:06,490
Matchless GO Players.

138
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:14,630
There's no problem with the entire concept.

139
00:10:14,630 --> 00:10:16,870
Recently, GO has slowly become more popular,

140
00:10:16,870 --> 00:10:18,670
especially after All-Around Challenge.

141
00:10:18,670 --> 00:10:21,830
Sheng Jingchu is really popular.

142
00:10:21,830 --> 00:10:23,760
I think your concept is really good.

143
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:28,010
If you need extra crews, equipment, budget,

144
00:10:28,010 --> 00:10:29,550
I'll personally obtain them on your behalf from the station.

145
00:10:29,550 --> 00:10:31,620
Thank you for your support Station Chief Gao.

146
00:10:31,620 --> 00:10:35,640
Xiao Cheng, don't be frustrated.

147
00:10:35,640 --> 00:10:39,820
Perhaps Matchless GO players could be the turning point for Cheng Yi Conversations.

148
00:10:39,820 --> 00:10:41,580
I'll try my very best.

149
00:10:41,580 --> 00:10:44,590
You can do it! We believe in you.

150
00:10:50,810 --> 00:10:53,300
Sister Cheng, bye-bye!

151
00:11:02,730 --> 00:11:04,600
Hurts! It hurts!

152
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:07,720
It hurts! It's me! It's me!

153
00:11:10,820 --> 00:11:14,700
Sis, you use too much force.

154
00:11:17,220 --> 00:11:19,730
You don't remember me?

155
00:11:19,730 --> 00:11:22,040
How did you know I was here?

156
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:23,620
I know you're a TV host.

157
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:26,620
In order to see you again, I've been giving out flyers here for days.

158
00:11:26,620 --> 00:11:28,700
What's going on? What are you doing?

159
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:30,810
What exactly do you want?

160
00:11:33,630 --> 00:11:35,940
- That day—
- That day? What "that day"?

161
00:11:35,940 --> 00:11:38,830
Don't be endlessly annoying.

162
00:11:38,830 --> 00:11:40,760
Sister,

163
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:44,200
I know that. You're mistaken.

164
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:48,260
Actually, I'm here to return the money.

165
00:11:48,260 --> 00:11:52,440
But I don't have money to pay you back now, so I can only write an IOU for you.

166
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:56,050
Forget it. You don't need to pay it back.

167
00:11:57,540 --> 00:11:58,590
[I owe you ¥5,000.]

168
00:11:58,590 --> 00:12:00,270
You wrote an extra zero, right?

169
00:12:00,270 --> 00:12:02,720
I only gave you ¥500 that day.

170
00:12:03,780 --> 00:12:06,440
I know that I wrote an extra zero.

171
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:09,290
No, wait... What do you mean by that?

172
00:12:15,370 --> 00:12:20,270
These days, I've kept working.

173
00:12:20,270 --> 00:12:24,150
I've been performing on the streets, passing out flyers, delivering food orders,

174
00:12:24,150 --> 00:12:26,080
doing all the work that can be done.

175
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:28,750
But I still can't make much money.

176
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:31,660
I can only eat one meal each day.

177
00:12:31,660 --> 00:12:34,230
I can only sleep in the cheapest place.

178
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:36,340
But there still isn't enough money.

179
00:12:36,340 --> 00:12:38,800
The ¥500 you gave me that day, after paying for the room,

180
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,520
I spent it really quickly.

181
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:42,390
So...

182
00:12:43,780 --> 00:12:46,670
the meaning for this IOU is...

183
00:12:49,220 --> 00:12:52,760
can you loan me another ¥4,500 to add up to ¥5,000 total?

184
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:55,890
- Do you think I'm stupid?
- It hurts. It hurts. Sis, it hurts!

185
00:12:55,890 --> 00:12:58,320
Sister, let go. It hurts!

186
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:01,630
Don't make trouble anymore, or I won't be polite anymore.

187
00:13:13,340 --> 00:13:16,020
What exactly do you want to do?

188
00:13:16,020 --> 00:13:18,180
I just want to learn GO.

189
00:13:18,180 --> 00:13:22,730
Why is it so hard?

190
00:13:22,730 --> 00:13:25,550
I don't want to just go back like this.

191
00:13:25,550 --> 00:13:30,230
I don't want my dream to be shattered just like this.

192
00:13:42,730 --> 00:13:44,280
That's all, Sister.

193
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:47,620
I was really so tired and sleepy. That's why I fell asleep.

194
00:14:28,850 --> 00:14:32,930
- Are you full?
- No.

195
00:14:32,930 --> 00:14:35,290
Boss, add an extra order here.

196
00:14:35,290 --> 00:14:37,070
Thank you, Sister.

197
00:14:39,060 --> 00:14:41,990
Is it worth it... to fight so hard?

198
00:14:41,990 --> 00:14:43,950
I don't know if it's worth it.

199
00:14:43,950 --> 00:14:46,610
But there is one thing, it's just that when I play GO,

200
00:14:46,610 --> 00:14:49,930
it's the time when I feel the most relaxed and happy.

201
00:14:52,790 --> 00:14:55,900
You remind me of when I just graduated

202
00:14:55,900 --> 00:14:57,950
and went to work as an intern at the TV station.

203
00:14:57,950 --> 00:15:01,390
No salary, not one of the official team, nothing at all.

204
00:15:01,390 --> 00:15:05,340
At that time, I almost didn't see any hope for the future.

205
00:15:05,340 --> 00:15:07,070
But I was the same as you are now,

206
00:15:07,070 --> 00:15:10,880
as long as I was focused on a road, I'd persist in walking it.

207
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:14,670
At that time, I rushed to do all the work in the TV station.

208
00:15:14,670 --> 00:15:18,370
Such as editing the video, writing the script, carrying the equipment,

209
00:15:18,370 --> 00:15:20,890
including working as an assistant to the TV anchor at the time.

210
00:15:20,890 --> 00:15:23,750
But precisely because of this process that accumulated experience,

211
00:15:23,750 --> 00:15:28,020
I was able to possess all the skills that a TV anchor should have.

212
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:33,380
Later, I finally got a chance to be on the screen.

213
00:15:33,380 --> 00:15:36,660
I used all those years of accumulated experience and conquered the audience,

214
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:39,800
employees, and the boss.

215
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:42,070
That's when I officially became

216
00:15:42,070 --> 00:15:44,180
a qualified TV host.

217
00:15:44,180 --> 00:15:47,000
So inspirational.

218
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:50,180
No wonder you're my goddess sister.

219
00:15:51,220 --> 00:15:55,980
I'm also feeling reflective about your current condition of loneliness and stubbornness.

220
00:15:55,980 --> 00:15:58,490
That's why I've said all this to you.

221
00:15:58,490 --> 00:16:02,270
I hope it can encourage you.

222
00:16:04,090 --> 00:16:06,070
Don't be afraid.

223
00:16:06,070 --> 00:16:09,230
Sometimes, it's when people are in a tight spot

224
00:16:09,230 --> 00:16:13,960
that there can be more possibilities for the future.

225
00:16:19,380 --> 00:16:23,520
Ever since I came back to the country, what you just said

226
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:26,090
are the warmest words I've heard.

227
00:16:26,090 --> 00:16:27,790
Thank you.

228
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:33,730
Thanks.

229
00:16:36,820 --> 00:16:38,430
Eat.

230
00:16:59,270 --> 00:17:02,400
Take your time eating. I've got things to do so I'll be leaving now.

231
00:17:03,510 --> 00:17:05,000
Where are you going? I'll take you.

232
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:08,050
No need. You go ahead and eat. I've already paid the check.

233
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:14,920
Mr. Sheng, I've noticed that after you've fallen in love,

234
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:16,830
you're finally starting to live a real life.

235
00:17:16,830 --> 00:17:18,650
